  "transcript": [
    {
      "id": "line-000",
      "start": 2.14,
      "end": 4.56,
      "text": "This is a labor box recording.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-001",
      "start": 5.42,
      "end": 8.24,
      "text": "All labor box recordings are in the public domain.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-002",
      "start": 9.2,
      "end": 13.8,
      "text": "For more information or to volunteer, please visit laborbox.org.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-003",
      "start": 14.54,
      "end": 18.32,
      "text": "Recorded by Patty McCoy in Hudson, Colorado.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-004",
      "start": 19.28,
      "end": 20.54,
      "text": "ASOPS Fables.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-005",
      "start": 21.78,
      "end": 23.5,
      "text": "Mercury and Sculpture.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-006",
      "start": 24.68,
      "end": 29.86,
      "text": "Mercury was very anxious to know in what estimation he was held by mankind.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-007",
      "start": 30.88,
      "end": 35.88,
      "text": "So he disguised himself as a man and walked into a sculptor's studio.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-008",
      "start": 37.02,
      "end": 41.28,
      "text": "Where there were a number of statues finished and ready for sale.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-009",
      "start": 42.66,
      "end": 47.68,
      "text": "Seeing a statue of Jupiter among the rest, he inquired the price of it.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-010",
      "start": 47.68,
      "end": 50.12,
      "text": "A crown said the sculpture.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-011",
      "start": 51.04,
      "end": 51.92,
      "text": "Is that all?",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-012",
      "start": 52.42,
      "end": 55.62,
      "text": "Said he laughing and pointing to one of Juno.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-013",
      "start": 56.28,
      "end": 57.24,
      "text": "How much is that one?",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-014",
      "start": 57.78,
      "end": 60.14,
      "text": "That was reply is half a crown.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-015",
      "start": 60.84,
      "end": 64.0,
      "text": "And how much right you be wanting for that one over there now?",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-016",
      "start": 64.7,
      "end": 67.86,
      "text": "He continued pointing to a statue of himself.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-017",
      "start": 68.44,
      "end": 73.88,
      "text": "That one said the sculpture, oh I'll throw him in for nothing, if you'll buy the other two.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-018",
      "start": 73.88,
      "end": 78.38,
      "text": "And of Mercury and Sculpture.",
      "note": ""
    }
  ],
